text.section:
An individual filing a new claim for unemployment insurance benefits establishing a new benefit year shall be advised of the following, at the time of filing such claim:
unemployment insurance benefits are subject to federal, State, and local income tax;
requirements exist pertaining to estimated tax payments;
the individual may elect to have the Secretary deduct federal income tax from the individual's payment of unemployment insurance benefits at the amount specified in the federal Internal Revenue Code;
the individual may elect to have the Secretary deduct State income tax from the individual's payment of unemployment insurance benefits at the rate of seven percent; and
the individual may change a previously elected withholding status.
